HEADWORD: Yamp
<hw>Yamp</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An
umbelliferous plant (<spn>Carum Gairdneri</spn>); also, its small fleshy
roots, which are eaten by the Indians from Idaho to
California.</def>⟦br⟧
